description:
"Exploring The Edges of Storytelling & Creativity" Keynote by Tiffany Shlain at the 2016 Gray Area Festival

What edges of storytelling and creativity are we pushing in todays world? In this opening keynote, Emmy-nominated filmmaker and Founder of The Webby Awards Tiffany Shlain offers a survey of some of the most exciting examples of pushing the edges of art and technology, ultimately exploring what they reveal about humanity and how we are shaping our world. She will then share her own experiments with art & technology with her teams cloud filmmaking adventures making collaborative films globally - ending the talk with their recent cloud film The Adaptable Mind.

The Gray Area Festival is four days of conference, performances, workshops, and exhibitions to discuss the impact of art and technology on culture. More at http://grayareafestival.io
